summary: I’ve been thinking back about how much I love Vox Machina and I realize that all I want now is a sitcom set in Whitestone...
body:
I’ve been thinking back about how much I love Vox Machina and I realize that all I want now is a sitcom set in Whitestone post-campaign. Plots include:

- The episode where they figure out that Grand Poobah was an actual title bestowed upon a leader in times of crisis in Whitestone centuries ago. Grog now outranks the De Rolo family and he is Determined to Have Fun

- In a similar vein: Vex legally registers Trinket as her son. Percy desperately tries to convince her not to give him control of Whitestone in the event of their passing.

- A rival bakery opens up shop right across the street from the Slayers Cake. Vox Machina must engage in a bake-off against the rival bakers to assert their dominance as Whitestone’s best bakery (they already have it written on the sign and everything)

- One of Percy and Vex’s children starts hanging out with Scanlan and is convinced that they want to become a bard. Percy Does Not Approve. Scanlan sits around in their house, playing obnoxious music and telling dirty jokes all day. Percy is Desperate to get their child to reconsider but Vex thinks its hilarious. (I’m thinking the kid is like 6 but im willing to negotiate that)

-Keyleth and the Sun Tree have their first fight. Keyleth is pretty torn up about it but the rest of Vox Machina spends the episode trying to convince everyone that she’s not just screaming at a tree.

-Just… Scanlan and Pike’s wedding… I want that episode.

summary: " I can count the seriously ill-meaning posts demanding Molls to be resurrected on one hand." then you haven't been looking hard...
question: " I can count the seriously ill-meaning posts demanding Molls to be resurrected on one hand." then you haven't been looking hard enough, the week after the funeral there were many post calling matt/the cast homophobic for not resurecting molly. being kind doen't mean letting people get away with things just beause they feel upset, specially when they choose to use the main tag/direct response to the cast on what their post
answer: Oh I know, I haven’t frogotten about that, but tbh I felt like there were more posts talking about those fans than actual fans doing that. Then again, I’m more active on Tumblr than Twitter or anything so maybe I missed most of it. I was just saying at this point it’s kinda water under the bridge imo, I haven’t heard about those issues again until today and the cast has been nothing but supportive of grieving fans. People were just acting out in anger, it happens. The cast didn’t deserve any of it and it was not an okay thing to do by any means, but they dealt with it like adults and as I said, I haven’t heard about it again until now. Thanks for talking to me about this, I appreciate that!
